A vintage 1960s technical illustration style image depicting an overflowing card catalog drawer with hundreds of index cards bursting out and spilling across a wooden desk, while multiple identical drawers behind it are being filled systematically by mechanical brass arms with gears and clockwork mechanisms. The cards have abstract symbols and geometric patterns instead of text. Warm sepia and amber tones with cream-colored cards, deep mahogany wood textures, and copper metallic accents on the machinery. The scene conveys the challenge of organizing massive amounts of data across limited storage spaces, with a sense of elegant mechanical problem-solving and organized chaos.
